## New Files Detail

### PM Coordinator Agent (`.claude/agents/pm-coordinator.md`)

- **Role**: Project Manager with full project context
- **Responsibilities**: Dashboard, roadmap management, research, delegation via `Task` tool, decision logging, RPI workflow
- **Skills**: `project-research` (web research), `roadmap-manager` (roadmap CRUD)
- **Context files read on start**: CLAUDE.md, backend/CLAUDE.md, frontend/CLAUDE.md, plans/ROADMAP.md, agent-comms.md, plans/DECISIONS.md

### Skills

**`project-research/SKILL.md`** — instructions for researching features, libs, and best practices via web
**`roadmap-manager/SKILL.md`** — instructions for reading/updating [plans/ROADMAP.md](file:///c:/Users/Fernando%20Prada/OneDrive%20-%20SVAN%20TRADING%20SL/Escritorio/Personal/Proyectos/TaxIA/plans/ROADMAP.md) and `plans/DECISIONS.md`

### `/pm` Command (`.claude/commands/pm.md`)

Steps: read all context → git status → present dashboard → interactive PM mode

---

## Migration Strategy

For each existing subagent:
1. Create new file in `.claude/agents/` with YAML frontmatter + existing body content (preserved as-is)
2. Keep `.claude/subagents/` as-is temporarily (for backward compatibility)
3. Update any references in `.claude/commands/` and `MULTI_AGENT_WORKFLOW.md`

> [!NOTE]
> The existing body content of each agent is already excellent (especially competitive and docscrawler). The migration only adds YAML frontmatter to enable Agent Teams features. The content stays the same.

---

## Verification

1. Test each migrated agent via its `/command`
2. Test PM agent: `/pm` → verify dashboard, research, delegation
3. Verify `Task` tool delegation from PM to other agents
